metadata.name: 420 BLAZE IT 1
metadata.description:
ok look if there's one thing web3 needs more of, it's nfts. specifically nfts that were made by a nonprofessional artist (me) using microsoft paint in approx 3 mins.

please keep this image in your wallet to show you're not a cop. like a cop wouldn't have this in their wallet bc cops aren't allowed to smoke weed, and this nft basically screams "i am a marijuana ally"

if i wanted to write an "artist statement" about this thing i'd be all like "the imagery hearkens back to aimless y2k youth rebellion but is set against the utopian capitalism represented by the zora zorb. the rough, handmade quality of the lettering --- self-conscious evidence of slapdash improvisation --- plays slyly against the eternal commemoration inherent to the nft format itself, yielding an art object which points towards its own objective subjectivity amid a landscape of blah blah blah hell yea 420 lol"
